description:
Location: Sheung Wan

Roles & responsibilities:

Lead an appointment unit to manage the corporate human resources matters pertaining to community services in Tung Wah including manpower planning, pay review, recruitment and appointment as well as staff discipline and complaints;
develop and implement human resources policies to meet the corporate objectives and service needs;
undertake regular review of personnel administration system and procedures as well as assigned ad hoc projects/tasks to cope with changing needs;
provide executive support to the secretarial office of the Human Resources Committee; and
undertake ad hoc projects and other general administrative duties including management of departmental business, supervision of staff and organization of meetings.

The ideal candidate should possess:

A recognized degree or equivalent, preferably human resources management;
at least Grade D in English Language (Syllabus B) and Chinese Language in the HKCEE or equivalent;
at least 4 years’ post-qualification administration experience, preferably human resources management/public administration;
proficiency in English and Chinese; and
good communication and interpersonal skills.

(Please specify in the application form the HKCEE result and relevant working experience you have attained in detail.)

Compensation & employment terms:

The successful candidate will initially be offered a 3-year contract with a remuneration package which will be commensurate with his/her background and experience.  The continuation of employment and employment terms thereafter will be subject to mutual agreement.  Apart from contributions to the MPF Scheme, other benefits include paid annual leave, medical services, a dental scheme and training sponsorships.  The incumbent will normally work under a 5-day week schedule subject to operational needs and exigencies of the service.

Application:

Please send your resume and a completed application form [F601(n)] with indication of your current and expected salaries to the Head of Human Resources Division, Tung Wah Group of Hospitals at 4/F., Wong Fung Ling Memorial Building, 12 Po Yan Street, Hong Kong by 20 January 2022.  Application forms are obtainable in person or can be downloaded from http://www.tungwah.org.hk.  The reference code should be marked both in the letter and on the envelope.  Underpaid mail items will not be accepted by Tung Wah.  For proper delivery of your mail items, please ensure your mail items bear sufficient postage with return address before posting.  Personal data provided by applicants will be used strictly for recruitment purpose only and in accordance with the Tung Wah’s personal data policy.  Applicants not invited to attend an interview by 30 April 2022 may assume that their applications are unsuccessful.

WE ARE AN EQUAL OPPORTUNITIES EMPLOYER

Perform HR and business data analysis. Prepare HR analytical and strategic planning report. Implementation of competitive reward and benefit practices and strategies. Accountable for various HR projects including annual bonus and salary review, staff promotion, and reward programs, performance management projects and manpower budget plan. Participate in market salary and benefit survey. Prepare material and data for management reports and meetings and support in review of HR policies and procedures to ensure the Bank is consistently complied with related regulatory requirements.

Requirements:

Degree holder in Human Resources Management or Business related disciplines with at least 2 years relevant experience, preferable in banking/ financial institution;

Strong analytical and organization skills with strategic mindset;
Proactive team player with excellent leadership and communication skills;
Able to handle multiple projects with tight deadlines;
Familiar with statutory and compliance requirements including Employment Ordinance and other relevant laws and regulations for Hong Kong and PRC;
Conversant with Chinese word processing and MS Office Suite especially in Excel and Access;
Proficient in both spoken and written English and Chinese, fluent in Putonghua is preferable.

If you are flexible enough and zeal for a harmonious and supportive working environment where enables you to grow and succeed professionally, please send a full resume indicating your public examination results (HKCEE and HKALE / HKDSE), your present and expected salary and quoting reference number attention to Talent Acquisition Division, Nanyang Commercial Bank, 151 Des Voeux Road Central, Hong Kong or apply through email. For details, please visit https://www.ncb.com.hk/ and select the page Recruit.

We are an Equal Opportunities Employer. Data collected would be used for recruitment purposes only. Applicants who do not hear from us within 8 weeks may consider their applications unsuccessful and their data will be destroyed within 12 months of receipt.

Responsibilities:

Provide all rounded clerical and administrative support;
Print and distribute HR statements or letters to staff;
Handle full spectrum of C&B functions and provide comprehensive HR services in a professional manner;
Perform C&B function e.g. monthly payroll, tax filing, MPF, insurance administration and benefits review;
To ensure the payroll and other payroll-related matters are proceeded with sufficient documentation and in compliance with company policies and Employment Ordinance;
Prepare various routine and ad-hoc HR data and analytics reports for management review;
Provide advice to superiors and answer general staff inquires regarding compensation & benefits;
Support the team in other HR duties as assigned.

Requirements:

Degree holder in Human Resources Management or other relevant disciplines
Minimum 3 years’ relevant experience in beauty industry and working experience in payroll and MPF administration
Experience in work injury (e.g. Form 2, 2A) handling will be an advantage
Well versed in Employment Ordinances and other relevant law and regulations
Excellent skill in Excel and other PC skills, including Chinese word processing
Proficient in both English and Chinese
Good numerical skills, Detail-minded and committed
Able to work under pressure, mature and independent
Immediate available is an advantage

Please apply in confidence with full resume, expected salary and availability by clicking “Apply Now” button.

You are invited to visit our website at: https://www.thebeauty.hk

The information provided will be used for selection purpose only. All information of unsuccessful applicants will be destroyed within six months.

Key Responsibilities:

Contribute to and ensure payroll process services quality are delivered in high quality timely manner;
Handle general enquiries and liaise with internal and external parties;
Preparing data and analysis to support key initiatives and projects;
Update and maintain human resources records and reports;
Provide all-round administrative support to HR department;
Perform ad-hoc tasks as required.

Requirements:

Higher Diploma or above in Human Resources Management or related discipline;
Experience in payroll process is an advantage;
Good communication skills, proactive, strong sense of responsibility, attention to details and able to work independently;
Proficiency in Microsoft Office (PowerPoint, Excel, Word and Chinese Word Processing) is a must;
Good command of both written and spoken English and Chinese;
Well-versed with Hong Kong Employment Ordinance and other related ordinances;
Immediate available is preferable.

Please send your application with full resume and expected salary to Human Resources Manager, Human Resources Department, 6/F, Tower B, Manulife Financial Centre, 223 Wai Yip Street, Kwun Tong, Kowloon, Hong Kong or by clicking "Apply Now".

Shuttle bus of the building is available at Lam Tin and Kwun Tong MTR Station.

Please visit our website www.buildking.hk for more details.
