Key Responsibilities



Reporting directly to the Country Manager(s), responsible for full spectrum of Hong Kong office’s HR and office administration; 
Acting as assistant to Hong Kong office’s Country Manager(s);
Responsible for end-to-end recruitment process to support hiring managers from manpower planning, job posting, conducting interviews, selection to post-employment follow up;
Maintain and administer an efficient and systematic procedure/system in keeping all HR records and confidential materials to ensure information security;
Prepare management and analysis reports for annual benchmarking on compensation packages, medical insurance scheme, job grading and evaluation through market research & data analysis;
Provide assistance to expatriates on work visa, relocation, housing, and tax arrangement;
Organize all business and travel arrangements including flight and hotel arrangement, visa application, travel insurance and expenses;
Support all office administration functions including but not limited to office moving & renovation, rental renewals, repair & maintenance and company's activities & any other ad hoc projects, etc.



Requirements


Diploma or above holder in Human Resources or related discipline;
Minimum 4 years of work experience in the HR field ideally from a garment sourcing/fashion company with set up experience in emerging markets;
Well-versed of Hong Kong employment ordinance and other statutory regulations related to employment;
Proficiency in MS Outlook, MS Word, Excel, and Powerpoint;
Excellent communications, interpersonal and negotiation skills;
Pleasant, mature, and committed with a high sense of work responsibility and ethics;
Self-motivated, well organized, patient & attentive to details with strong numerical and analytical skills;
Strong time management and multi-tasking skills and ability to cope with work pressure in a fast pace environment to meet strict deadlines;
Ability to work independently with minimal supervision, positive with a can-do attitude;
Team players and able to create a harmonious and positive work atmosphere;
Excellent command of written and spoken English

What we offer


Excellent development and career growth opportunity;
Multinational and open-minded work environment;
Competitive remuneration and benefits.

Responsibilities:

Responsible for full spectrum of HR functions including but not limited to new staff on-boarding and departure processes, payroll processing, compensation & benefits, performance management, employee relations for designated functions;
Handle internal customer enquiries in a timely and professional manner;
Maintain staff records and manage data in HRIS on regular basis;
Formulate and update HR policies and procedures from time to time in compliance with the relevant statutory legislation;
Provide professional advice to all levels on HR policies and enquiries on HR areas;
Maintain and prepare HR reports and analysis for management review;
Handle ad hoc duties and projects as assigned;

Together with reliable, integrity and passion, our ideal staff should meet the following requirements:

Degree holder in Human Resources Management or related disciplines;
Minimum 5 years of relevant working experience;
Sound knowledge in HR practices, labor ordinance & related legal regulatory;
Positive thinking with strong problem-solving, organizational and communication skills;
Independent, able to work under pressure and cope with a fast-paced environment;
Proficient in MS Applications and Chinese word processing

Interested parties, please send your application with detailed resume stating expected salary and date of availability by clicking "APPLY NOW'.

