[REF: SHRM(P)1/SAHRM(A)/JOBS]

Location: Sheung Wan

Roles & responsibilities:

Plan, design, develop and implement staff relations and welfare policies to align with the corporate strategies;
oversee the handling of staff welfare benefits (such as medical/dental treatment, merit awards and etc.), make recommendations for applications of staff welfare schemes/grants and ensure all applications are processed in a timely and proper manner;
manage staff awards such as Long Service Awards, Retirement Awards by designing the souvenir(s) and follow up the production and distribution;
plan and formulate the office yearly plan/budget of the Section for management’s approval;
conduct review to smoothen the operation procedure of the Section and provide recommendations to optimize the staff welfare benefit schemes/grants;
consolidate the regular/annual exercises (i.e. annual report/plan/budget) for the Section and prepare the integrated version for management’s approval;
lead the Administration Team to maintain a smooth daily office operation for the Section; and
plan, design and implement staff welfare/relations initiatives as assigned.

The ideal candidate should possess:

a recognized degree or equivalent;
at least Grade D in English Language (Syllabus B) and Chinese Language in the HKCEE or equivalent;
at least 4 years of administrative experience preferably in drafting administration policy/staff welfare schemes or project management;
proficiency in English and Chinese, and preferably in Putonghua;
calibre as a good team player with supervisory experience and sound communication skills; and
ability to work independently with initiative and have a strong sense of responsibility.

(Please specify in the application form the HKCEE result and relevant working experience you have attained in detail.)

Compensation & employment terms:

The successful candidate will initially be offered a 3-year contract with a remuneration package which will be commensurate with his/her background and experience.  The continuation of employment and employment terms thereafter will be subject to mutual agreement.  Apart from contributions to the MPF Scheme, other benefits include paid annual leave, medical services, a dental scheme and training sponsorships.  The incumbent will normally work under a 5-day week schedule subject to operational needs and exigencies of the service.

Application:

Please send your resume and a completed application form [F601(n)] with indication of your current and expected salaries to the Head of Human Resources Division, Tung Wah Group of Hospitals at 4/F., Wong Fung Ling Memorial Building, 12 Po Yan Street, Hong Kong by 24 January 2022.  The reference code should be marked both in the letter and on the envelope.  Application forms are obtainable in person or can be downloaded from http://www.tungwah.org.hk.  Underpaid mail items will not be accepted by Tung Wah.  For proper delivery of your mail items, please ensure your mail items bear sufficient postage with return address before posting.  Personal data provided by applicants will be used strictly for recruitment purpose only and in accordance with the Tung Wah's personal data policy.  Applicants not invited to attend an interview by 30 April 2022 may assume that their applications are unsuccessful.

WE ARE AN EQUAL OPPORTUNITIES EMPLOYER

*Candidate with more experience will be considered as Manager.


 Responsibilities: 

Perform full spectrum of Human Resources functions;
Handle payroll calculation, taxation, MPF administration and staff attendance record;

Responsible for recruitment & selection, compensation & benefits administration, performance management and employee relations;
Responsible for review, development and implementation of company policies/procedures pertaining to resources management;
Perform ad hoc assignments and projects as assigned by management to support the business goals.

Requirements:

Higher Diploma or above in Human Resources Management, Business Administration or relevant disciplines;
Minimum 3 year of relevant working experience, preferably in Construction and Engineering industry;
Well versed in HK employment Ordinances and related legislation;
Highly organized, trust-worthy and independent;
Good command of written and spoken  English, Chinese & Mandarin;
Good interpersonal, strong communication and negotiation skills;
Able to work under pressure and result oriented;
Immediate available is highly preferred.

We offer reasonable remuneration packages, include year-end bonus, annual leave, public holiday, 5.5 day work / 6 day  (alternative leave), as well as good career prospects for the right applicant. Interested parties, welcome to browse to our web site hk-egg.com, and send detail resume with expected salary & date availability by clicking "Apply Now" 

Personal data will be used for recruitment purpose only.

